obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43020)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43020&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Bengal, ^1[Agra] and Assam`
  line `Civil Courts Act, 1887.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the territories ^2[which were on the 11th March, 1887,] respectively`
  line `administered by the Lieutenant-Governor of Bengal, the Lieutenant-Governor of the NorthWestern Provinces and the Chief Commissioner of Assam, except such portions of those`
  line `territories as for the time being are not subject to the ordinary civil jurisdiction of the High`
  line `Courts ^3***; and`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of July, 1887.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1911, s. 2, for "North-Western Provinces".`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "for the time being".`
  line
  line `3. The words "and except the Jhansi Division" rep. by Act 20 of 1890, s. 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43021)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43021&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line ^2
  line `*** all Courts constituted, appointments, nominations, rules and orders made,`
  line `jurisdiction and powers conferred and lists published under the Bengal Civil Courts Act,`
  line `1871 (6 of 1871) ^3`
  line `, or any enactment thereby repealed, or purporting expressly or impliedly`
  line `to have been so constituted, made, conferred and published, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `respectively constituted, made, conferred and published under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(3) Any enactment or document referring to the Bengal Civil Courts Act, 1871 (6 of 1871)7`
  line `, or to any`
  line `enactment thereby repealed, shall be construed to refer to this Act or to the corresponding portion thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-section (1) rep. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. The word "But" rep. s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Act 6 of 1871 was rep. by s. 2 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43022)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Classes of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43022&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `There shall be the following classes of Civil Courts under this Act, namely:`
  line
  line `(1) the Court of the District Judge;`
  line
  line `(2) the Court of the Additional Judge;`
  line
  line `(3) the Court of the Subordinate Judge; and`
  line
  line `(4) the Court of the Munsif.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment in Section-3 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil Courts Act, 1887 (Act 12 of`
  line `1887).-- In Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil Courts Act 1887 (Act, 12 of 1887) (herein after referred to as`
  line `the said Act) in Clause-(3) of Section-3 for the words "Subordinate Judge" words and bracket "Civil`
  line `Judge (Senior Division)" and in Clause (4) for the words "Munsif" the words and bracket "Civil Judge`
  line `(Junior Division)" shall be substituted"`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 14 of 2014, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43023)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Number of District Judges, Subordinate Judges and Munsifs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule, for section 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43023&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[4. Number of District Judges, Subordinate Judges and Munsifs.—The State Government may`
  line `alter the number of District Judges, Subordinate Judges and Munsifs now fixed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43024)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `[Repealed.] .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43024&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `[Number of Munsifs.] Rep. by the Decentralization Act, 1914 (4 of 1914), s. 2 and the Schedule,`
  line `Part I.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43025)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vacancies among District or Subordinate Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43025&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the office of District`
  line `Judge or Subordinate Judge is vacant by reason of the death, resignation or removal of the Judge or`
  line `other cause, or whenever ^1[an increase in the number of District or Subordinate Judges has been`
  line `made under the provisions of section 4], the ^2[State Government or, as the case may be, the High`
  line `Court] may fill up the vacancy or appoint the additional District Judges or Subordinate Judges`
  line ^3***.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be construed to prevent a State Government from appointing a`
  line `District Judge or Subordinate Judge to discharge, for such period as it thinks fit, in addition to the`
  line `functions devolving on him as such District Judge or Subordinate Judge, all or any of the functions`
  line `of another District Judge or Subordinate Judge, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6 of Act XII of 1887.--In section 6 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil`
  line `Court Act, 1887, herein after in this chapter referred to as the principal Act, in sub -section (2), for`
  line `the words "state Government" the words "High Court" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 17 of 1991, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 2 and the First Schedule, ibid., for the G.G. in C. has sanctioned an increase of the number of District Judges or`
  line `Subordinate Judges.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for dqtsL. G"..`
  line
  line `3. The words as the case may be rep. by ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (43026)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `[Repealed.] .`
  content `[Vacancies among Munsifs.] Rep.by the A. O. 1937.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43026&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (43027)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Additional Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43027&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the business pending before any District Judge requires the`
  line `aid of Additional Judges for its speedy disposal, the State Government may, ^1[having consulted] the`
  line `High Court ^2***, appoint such Additional Judges as may be requisite.`
  line
  line `(2) Additional Judges so appointed shall discharge any of the functions of a District Judge which the`
  line `Disrict Judge may assign to them, and, in the discharge of those functions, they shall exercise the same`
  line `powers as the District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs., ibid., for "upon the recommendation of".`
  line
  line `2. The words "and with the previous sanction of the G. G. in C." rep. by Act 16 of 1911, s. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (43028)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Administrative control of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43028&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the superintendence of the High Court, the District`
  line `Judge shall have administrative control over all the Civil Courts under this Act within the local limits of`
  line `his jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (43029)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Temporary charge of District Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43029&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of the death, resignation or removal`
  line `of the District Judge, or of his being incapacitated by illness or otherwise for the performance of his`
  line `duties, or of his absence from the place at which his Court is held, the Additional Judge, or, if an`
  line `Additional Judge is not present at that place, the senior Subordinate Judge present thereat, shall,`
  line `without relinquishing his ordinary duties, assume charge of the office of the District Judge, and that`
  line `continue in charge thereof until the office is resumed by the District Judge or assumed by an officer`
  line `appointed thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) While in charge of the office of the District Judge, the Additional Judge or Subordinate Judge, as`
  line `the case may be, may, subject to any rules which the High Court may make in this behalf, exercise any of`
  line `the powers of the District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (43030)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Transfer of proceedings on vacation of office of Subordinate Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43030&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of`
  line `the death, resignation or removal of a Subordinate Judge, or of his being incapacitated by illness or`
  line `otherwise for the performance of his duties, or of his absence from the place at which his Court is`
  line `held, the District Judge may transfer all or any of the proceedings pending in the Court of the`
  line `Subordinate Judge either to his own Court or to any Court under his administrative control competent`
  line `to dispose of them.`
  line
  line `(2) Proceedings transferred under sub-section (1) shall be disposed of as if they had been instituted in`
  line `the Court to which they are so transferred:`
  line
  line `(3) Provided that the District Judge may re-transfer to the Court of the Subordinate Judge or his`
  line `successor any proceedings transferred under sub-section (1) to his own or any other Court.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of proceedings which are not pending in the Court of the Subordinate Judge`
  line `on the occurrence of an event referred to in sub-section (1), and with respect to which that Court has`
  line `exclusive jurisdiction, the District Judge may exercise all or any of the jurisdiction of that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (43031)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `[Repealed.] .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43031&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `[Temporary charge of office of Munsif.] Rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of Act no. 12 of 1887.-- In the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil Courts Act,`
  line `1887hereinafter referred to as the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in Section 3, 4, 6, 10, 11, 13, 18, 21, 22, 23, 24 and 25, for the words "Civil`
  line `Judge" and "Civil Judges" wherever occurring, the words "Civil Judge (Senior Division)"`
  line `and "CivilJudges (Senior Division)" shall respectively be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in Sections 3, 4, 13, 19, 21, 22, 23, 24 and 25, for the words "Munsif" an`
  line `"Munsifs" wherever occurring, the words "Civil Judge (Junior Division)" and "Civil`
  line `Judges (Junior Division)" shall respectively be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) for the existing marginal headings to the sections shown in Column I of the table below,`
  line `the marginal headings as shown in Column II thereof shall be substituted, namely :--`
  line
  line `Section Marginal headings as hereby substituted`
  line
  line `4 Number of District Judges; Civil Judges (Senior`
  line `Division) and Civil Judges (Junior Division)`
  line
  line `6 Vacancies among District or Civil Judge (SeniorDivision)`
  line
  line `11 Transfer of proceedings on vacation of office of CivilJudge (Senior`
  line `Division)`
  line
  line `18 Extent of original jurisdiction of District or Civil Judge`
  line `(Senior Division)`
  line
  line `19 Extent of jurisdiction of Civil Judge (Junior Division)`
  line
  line `21 Appeals from Civil Judges (Senior Division) and Civil`
  line `Judges (Junior Division)`
  line
  line `22 Power to transfer to Civil Judges (Senior Division)appeal from Civil`
  line `Judges (Junior Division)`
  line
  line `23 Exercise by Civil Judge (Senior Division) or Civil Judge (Junior division)`
  line `of jurisdiction of District Court in certain proceedings.`
  line
  line `25 Power to invest Civil Judges (Senior Division) and Civil Judges (Junior`
  line `Division) with Small Cause Court Jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 25 of 1995, s. 2]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of section 12 of 1887.-- In the said Act, the word "Subordinate Judge" and the word`
  line `"Munsif" wherever used shall be substituted by the words and bracket "Civil Judge (Senior Division)"`
  line `and "Civil Judge (Junior Division)" respectively.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 14 of 2014, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (43032)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to fix local limits of jurisdiction of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43032&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, fix and alter the local limits of the jurisdiction of any Civil Court`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If the same local jurisdiction is assigned to two or more Subordinate Judges or to two or more`
  line `Munsifs, the District Judge may assign to each of them such civil business cognizable by the Subordinate`
  line `Judge or Munsif, as the case may be, as, subject to any General or special orders of the High Court, he`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) When civil business arising in any local area is assigned by the District Judge under`
  line `sub-section (2) to one of two or more Subordinate Judges, or to one of two or more Munsifs, a`
  line `decree or order passed by the Subordinate Judge or Munsif shall not be invalid by reason only of the`
  line `case in which it was made having arisen wholly or in part in a place beyond the local area if that`
  line `place is within the local limits fixed by the State Government under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) A Judge of a Court of Small Causes appointed to be also a Subordinate Judge or Munsif is a`
  line `Subordinate Judge or Munsif, as the case may be, within the meaning of this section.`
  line
  line `(5) The present local limits of the jurisdiction of every Civil Court under this Act shall be deemed to`
  line `have been fixed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (43033)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Place of sitting of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43033&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, fix and alter the place or places at which any Civil Court under this Act is to be held.`
  line
  line `(2) All places at which any such Courts are now held shall be deemed to have been fixed under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (43034)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Vacations of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43034&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such orders as may be made ^1*** ^2[*** by the State`
  line `Government ^3*** ] the High Court shall prepare a list of days to be observed in each year as close`
  line `holidays in the Civil Courts.`
  line
  line `(2) The list shall be published in the official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) A judicial act done by a Civil Court on a day specified in the list shall not be invalid by reason`
  line `only of its having been done on that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "by the G.G. in C., in the case of the High Court at Calcutta, and " rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. The words "in other cases" rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (43035)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Seals of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43035&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Every Civil Court under this Act shall use a seal of such form and dimensions`
  line `as are prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (43036)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Continuance of proceedings of Courts ceasing to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43036&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any`
  line `Civil Court under this Act has from any cause ceased to have jurisdiction with respect to any`
  line `case, any proceeding in relation to that case which, if that Court had not ceased to have`
  line `jurisdiction, might have been had therein may be had in the Court to which the business of the`
  line `former Court has been transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section applies to cases for which provision is made in section 623 o r`
  line `section 649 of the Code of Civil Procedure^1 (14 of 1882) or in any other enactment for the`
  line `time being in force.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17.-- In sub-section (2) of section 17 of the said Act, for the words and figures`
  line `"in Section 623 or Section 649 of the Code of Civil Procedure" the words and figures "in sections 36, 37`
  line `and 114 of, and Rule 1 of Order XLVII in Schedule I to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 6 of 1935, s. 3]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 17 of Act XII of 1887.-- In sub-section (2) of Section 17 of the Bengal,`
  line `Agra and Assam Civil Courts Act, 1887 (XII of 1887) (hereinafter referred to as the said Act), for the`
  line `words and figures "in Section 623 or Section 649 of the Code of Civil Procedure" the words and figures`
  line `"in Sections 36, 37 and 114 of, and Rule 1 of Order XLVII in Schedule I to the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 12 of 1960, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. In Bengal and Assam, for the words and figures "in s. 623 or s. 649 of the Code of Civil Procedure" the words`
  line `and figures "in ss. 36, 37 and 114 of, and rule 1 of Order XLVII in Sch. I to, the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908,"`
  line `have been subs. by Bengal Act 19 of 1935 and Assam Act 6 of 1935, respectively. In Agra, Bihar and Orissa,`
  line `also, the reference to the old enactment should be construed in the same way: see the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (Act 5 of 1908), s. 158.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (43037)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Extent of original jurisdiction of District or Subordinate Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43037&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise`
  line `provided by any enactment for the time being in force, the jurisdiction of a District Judge or`
  line `Subordinate Judge extends, subject to the provisions of section 15 of the Code of Civil`
  line Procedure^1
  line `(14 of 1882), to all original suits for the time being cognizable by Civil Courts.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 18 and 39.-- In Section 18 of the Said Act, after the words "Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure", the figures "1908" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 6 of 1935, s. 4]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 18 of Act XII of 1887. -- In Section 18 of the said Act, after the words "Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure", the figures "1908" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 12 of 1960, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. In Bengal and Assam, the figures "1908," have been ins. at this place by Bengal Act 19 of 1935 and Assam Act 6`
  line `of 1935, respectively. In Agra, Bihar and Orissa. also, the reference to the old enactment should be construed in`
  line `the same way: see the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908), s. 158.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (43038)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Extent of jurisdiction of Munsif.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43038&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^119.Extent of jurisdiction of Munsif.--(1) Save as aforesaid, and subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2), the jurisdiction of a Munsif extends to all like suits of which the`
  line `value does not exceed one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, on the recommendation of the High Court, direct, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, with respect to any Munsif named therein, that his`
  line `jurisdiction shall extend to all like suits of such value not exceeding two thousand rupe es as`
  line `may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, delegate`
  line `to the High Court its powers under this section.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19.-- In sub-section (2) of section 19 of the said Act, for the words`
  line `beginning with "that his jurisdiction" and ending with "in the notification" the following shall`
  line `be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(a) that his jurisdiction shall extend to all like suits of such value not exceeding two`
  line `thousand rupees as may be specified in the notification, or`
  line
  line `(b) that so long as he holds Court at a place where the Court of a Subordinate Judge is`
  line `held his jurisdiction shall extend to all like suits of such value not exceeding three`
  line `thousand rupees as may be so specified."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 6 of 1935, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19.-- In the Principal Act, in Section 19--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), for the words "seven thousand rupees" , the words "fifty thousand rupees"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2), for the words "twenty five thousand rupees" the words "two lakhs rupees"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 44 of 2005, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19.-- In section 19 of the principal Act, --`
  line
  line `(1) in sub-section (1), for the words "one thousand rupees at the end the words three thousand`
  line `rupees" shall be substituted:`
  line
  line `(2) for sub-section (2) the following shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) The State Government may, on the recommendation of the High Court, direct, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette with respect to any Munsif named therein that his jurisdiction shall`
  line `extend to all like suits of such value not exceeding five thousand rupees as may be specified in the`
  line `notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, delegate to the`
  line `High Court its powers under this section."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam 9 of 1965, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19.--(1) In section 19 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), for the words`
  line `"three thousand rupees" the words "seven thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(2) In section 19 of the principal act, in sub-section (2) for the words "ten thousand rupees" the words`
  line `"twentyfive thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 7 of 1993, s. 2]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand
  line
  line `Amendment of sub-section (2) of section 19.--In sub-section (2) of section 19 of the Bengal, Agra`
  line `and assam Civil Courts Act, 1887--`
  line
  line `"(2) Words 'one lac' for the words 'twenty five thousand' shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttaranchal Act 20 of 2005, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19 of act 12 of 1887.--for section 19 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil`
  line `Courts Act, 1887, hereinafter in this Chapter referred to as the principal Act, the following section shall`
  line `be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"19 (1) Save as aforesaid, and subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the jurisdiction of a`
  line `Munsif extends to all like suits of which the value dose not exceed five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, on the recommendation of the High Court, direct by notification`
  line `in the official Gazette, with respect to any Munsif named therein, that his jurisdiction shall extend to`
  line `all like suits of such value not exceeding ten thousand rupees as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, the notification in the official Gazette, delegate to the`
  line `High Court its powers under this section."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 57 of 1976, s. 27]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19.--In section 19 of the principal Act,-`
  line
  line `(a)-in sub-section (1), for the words five thousand rupees the words ten thousand rupees shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(b)-for sub-section (2), the following sub-section shall be substituted namely:-`
  line
  line `(2) the High Court may direct by notification in the official Gazette, with respect to any music`
  line `named therein, that his Jurisdiction shall extend to all like suits of such value not exceeding twenty`
  line `five thousand rupees as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 17 of 1991, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19 of Act no. XII of 1887.-- In section 19 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil`
  line `Court Act, 1887 hereinafter in this Chapter referred to as the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1) for the words "ten thousand rupees" the words "one lakh rupees" shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2) for the words "twenty five thousand rupees" the words "five lakh rupees"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 14 of 2015, s. 2 ]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 19 of Act 12 of 1887. -- In Section 19 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil`
  line `Courts Act, 1887 (Act 12 of 1887) (hereinafter referred to as the said Act).`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1) for the words "two thousand" the words "twenty thousand" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2) for the words "five thousand" the words "thirty thousand" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 19 of 1987, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19 of the Act, 12 of 1887.-- In the said Act in Section-19 the words`
  line `"the Jurisdiction of Munsif extends to all like suits of which the value does not exceed Thirty thousand`
  line `rupees" shall be substituted by the words, numbers and bracket the Jurisdiction of Civil Judge (Junior`
  line `Division) extends to all like suits of which the value does not exceed rupees 1,50,000/-(One lac fifty`
  line `thousand rupees)".`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 14 of 2014, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 19 of Act XII of 1887. -- In Section 19 of the said Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), for the words "one thousand", the words "two thousand" shall be substituted;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2), for the words "four thousand", the words "five thousand" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 12 of 1960, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 19 does not apply to Honorary Munsifs and Benches, in the U. P.: see the U. P. Honorary Munsifs Act, 1896`
  line `(U.P. 2 of 1896), s. 13. This section has been diversely amended in Bengal, Bihar and Orissa, Agra and Assam`
  line `by Ben. Act 19 of 1935, s. 5, B. & O. Act 4 of 1922, s. 2, U.P. Act 5 of 1925, ss. 2 and 3, and Assam Act 6 of`
  line `1935, s. 5, respectively.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule, Part I.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (43039)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Appeals from District and Additional Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43039&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided by`
  line `any enactment for the time being in force, an appeal from a decree or orderof a District`
  line `Judge or Additional Judge shall lie to the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal shall not lie to the High Court from a decree or order of an Additional Judge in any`
  line `case in which, if the decree or order had been made by the District Judge,`
  line `an appeal would not lie to that`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (43040)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Appeals from Subordinate Judges and Munsifs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43040&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as aforesaid, an appeal from a`
  line `decree or order of a Subordinate Judge shall lie--`
  line
  line `(a) to the District Judge where the value of the original suit in which or in any proceeding`
  line `arising out of which the decree or order was made did not exceed five thousand rupees, and`
  line
  line `(b) to the High Court in any other case.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as aforesaid, an appeal from a decree or order of a Munsif shall lie to the District Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the function of receiving any appeals which lie to the District Judge under sub-section (1)`
  line `or sub-section (2) has been assigned to an Additional Judge, the appeals may bepreferred to the`
  line `Additional Judge.`
  line
  line `(4) The High Court may, with the previous sanction of the State Government, direct, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, that appeals lying to the District Judge under sub-section (2) from all or any of the`
  line `decrees or orders of any Munsif shall be preferred to the Court of such Subordinate Judge as may be`
  line `mentioned in the notification, and the appeals shall thereupon be preferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 21.---In the Principal Act, in section 21, in sub-section (1), in`
  line `clause (a), for the words "fifty thousand rupees" the words "five lakh rupees" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `(a) to the District Judge where the value of the original suit in which or in any`
  line `proceeding arising out of which, the decree or order was made, whether instituted or commenced or decided before or after the commencement of the Uttar Pradesh Civil Laws`
  line `Amendment Act, 1968, was less than twenty thousand rupees; and`
  line
  line `(b) to the High Court, in any other case.`
  line
  line `(I-A) An appeal from a decree or order of Civil Judge where the value of the original`
  line `suit in which, or in any proceeding arising out of which, the decree or order was made`
  line `exceeded ten thousand rupees but was less than twenty-thousand rupees instituted in the`
  line `High Court before the date of commencement of the Uttar Pradesh Civil Laws Amendment`
  line `Act, 1970, and pending in the High Court immediately before the said date, not being an`
  line `appeal in which arguments have been concluded before the said date and only judgment`
  line `disposing of the appeal remains to be pronounced, shall stand transferred to the District`
  line `Judge having jurisdiction who may either decide it himself or assign it to any Additional`
  line `Judge sub-ordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(I-B) The period of limitation prescribed for filing an appeal from a decree or order of a`
  line `Civil Judge where the value of the original suit in which, or in any proceeding arising out of`
  line `which, the decree or order was made exceeded ten thousand rupees but was less than twenty`
  line `thousand rupees and the decree or order was made before December 2, 1968, shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything in the Limitation Act, 1963, be deemed to be and always to have`
  line `been the same as if the appeal continued to lie to the High Court."`
  line
  line `(b) to the High Court, in any other case.`
  line
  line `(I-A) An appeal from a decree or order of Civil Judge where the value of the original`
  line `suit in which, or in any proceeding arising out of which, the decree or order was made`
  line `exceeded ten thousand rupees but was less than twenty-thousand rupees instituted in the`
  line `High Court before the date of commencement of the Uttar Pradesh Civil Laws Amendment`
  line `Act, 1970, and pending in the High Court immediately before the said date, not being an`
  line `appeal in which arguments have been concluded before the said date and only judgment`
  line `disposing of the appeal remains to be pronounced, shall stand transferred to the District`
  line `Judge having jurisdiction who may either decide it himself or assign it to any Additional`
  line `Judge sub-ordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(I-B) The period of limitation prescribed for filing an appeal from a decree or order of`
  line `a Civil Judge where the value of the original suit in which, or in any proceeding arising out`
  line `of which, the decree or order was made exceeded ten thousand rupees but was less than`
  line `twenty thousand rupees and the decree or order was made before December 2, 1968, shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything in the Limitation Act, 1963, be deemed to be and always to have`
  line `been the same as if the appeal continued to lie to the High Court."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 44 of 2005, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 21.--In section 21 of the principal Act, in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1), for the words "five thousand rupees" the words "seven thousand rupees" shall`
  line `be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 9 of 1965, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 21.--In section 21 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), in clause`
  line `(a), for the words "twenty thousand rupees", the words "fifty thousand rupees" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 7 of 1993, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 21 of Act XII of 1887.--In section 21 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil`
  line `Courts Act, 1887, as amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh (hereinafter referred to as the Bengal,`
  line `Agra and Assam Civil Courts Act), for sub-section (1), the following sub-section shall be substituted,`
  line `namely :--`
  line
  line `"(1) Save as aforesaid, an appeal from a decree or order of a Civil Judge shall lie--`
  line
  line `(a) to the District Judge where the value of the original suit in which or in any proceeding arising`
  line `out of which, the decree or order was made, whether instituted or commenced or decided before or`
  line `after the commencement of the Uttar Pradesh Civil Laws Amendment Act, 1968, was less than`
  line `twenty thousand rupees; and`
  line
  line `(b) to the High Court, in any other case.`
  line
  line `(I-A) An appeal from a decree or order of a Civil Judge where the value of the original suit in which,`
  line `or in any proceeding arising out of which, the decree or order was made exceeded ten thousand rupees but`
  line `was less than twenty thousand rupees instituted in the High Court before the date of commencement of`
  line `the Uttar Pradesh Civil Laws Amendment Act, 1970 and pending in the High Court immediately before`
  line `the said date, not being an appeal in which arguments have been concluded before the said date and only`
  line `judgement disposing of the appeal remains to be pronounced, shall stand transferred to the District Judge`
  line `having jurisdiction who may either decide it himself or assign it to any Additional Judge subordinate to`
  line him.
  line
  line `(I-B) The period of limitation prescribed for filing an appeal from a decree or order of a Civil Judge`
  line `where the value of the original suit in which, or in any proceeding arising out of which, the decree or`
  line `order was made exceeded ten thousand rupees but was less than twenty thousand rupees and the decree or`
  line `order was made before December 2, 1968, shall notwithstanding anything in the Limitation Act, 1963, be`
  line `deemed to be and always to have been the same as if the appeal continued to lie to the High Court."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 14 of 1970, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 21--In section 21 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-sections (1), (1-A) and (1-B), the following sub-sections shall be`
  line `substituted, namely :--`
  line
  line `(1) Save as aforesaid an appeal from a decree or order of a Civil Judge shall lie,-`
  line
  line `(a) to the High Court in any case other than a case referred to in clause (b) ;`
  line
  line `(b) to the District Judge where the value of the original suit in which or in any`
  line `proceeding arising out of which the decree or order was made (either instituted or`
  line `commenced before or after the relevant date) did not exceed one lakh rupees or such`
  line `higher amount not exceeding five lakh rupees as the High Court may fix from time to`
  line `time by notification in the official Gazette.`
  line
  line `Explanation-- For the purposes of this sub-section and sub-section (1-A) and`
  line `(1-B) relevant date means the date of commencement of the Uttar Pradesh Civil`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 1991 or, as the case may be, the date of commencement`
  line `of notification made under clause (b) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(1-A) An appeal, from a decree or order of a Civil Judge where the value of`
  line `the original suit in which, or in any proceeding arising out of which the decree or`
  line `order was made was not more than amount fixed by or under clause (b) of subsection (1) instituted in High Court and pending in the High Court immediately`
  line `before the relevant date, shall stand transferred to the District judge having`
  line `jurisdiction who may either decide it himself or assign it to any additional Judge`
  line `subordinate to him :`
  line
  line `Provided that any judgment, decree or order passed in such an appeal by the`
  line `High Court after the relevant date shall be valid as if the High Court had`
  line `withdrawn the appeal under section 24 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908.`
  line
  line `(1-B) The period of limitation prescribed for filing an appeal from a decree or`
  line `order of a Civil Judge made before the relevant date, which lay to the High Court immediately before such date but lies to the District Judge under subsection (1) shall not withstanding anything to the contrary contained in the`
  line `Limitation Act, 1963, be deemed to be and always to have been the same as if the`
  line `appeal continued to lieto the High Court.";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4), the words "with the previous sanction of the State`
  line `Government,' shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 17 of 1991, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 21.In section 21 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), in clause (b),-`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "one lakh rupees" the words "five lakh rupees" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "five lakh rupees" the words "twenty-five lakh rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[VideUttar Pradesh Act 14 of 2015, s. 3]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 21 of Act XII of 1887.--In clause (a) of sub-section (1) of Section 21 of the`
  line `Bengal, Agra & Assam Civil Courts Act, 1887 (XII of 1887), for the words "did not exceed five thousand`
  line `rupees", the word "was less than ten thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 1959, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 21 of Act 12 of 1887.--In the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil Courts`
  line `Act, 1887 (Act 12 of 1887) clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 21 for the words "sixty`
  line `thousand" the words "two lakhs" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 19 of 1996, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment in section 21 of the Act, 12 of 1887.--In the said act in Clause (a) of sub-section`
  line `(1) of section-21 the words "Two lacs rupees" shall be substituted by the number, bracket and`
  line `words "rupees 10,000/-(rupees Ten lacs)"`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 14 of 2014, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Amendment in section 21 of Act 12 of 1887.--In section (a) of sub-section (1) of Section 21`
  line `of the said Act of the words "ten thousand" the words "sixty thousand" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 19 of 1987, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (43041)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to transfer to Subordinate Judges appeals from Munsifs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43041&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) A District Judge may`
  line `transfer to any Subordinate Judge under his administrative control any appeals pending before him from`
  line `the decrees or orders of Munsifs.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Judge may withdraw any appeal so transferred, and either hear and dispose of it`
  line `himself or transfer it to a Court under his administrative control competent to dispose of it.`
  line
  line `(3) Appeals transferred under this section shall be disposed of subject to the rules`
  line `applicable to like appeals when disposed of by the District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (43129)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Exercise by Subordinate Judge or Munsif of jurisdiction of District Court in certain proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43129&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^123. Exercise by Subordinate Judge or Munsif of jurisdiction of district Court in certain`
  line `proceedings.--(1) The High Court may, by general or special order, authorize any Subordinate`
  line `Judge or Munsif to take cognizance of, or any district Judge to transfer to a Subordinate Judge or`
  line `Munsif under his administrative control, any of the proceedings next hereinafter mentioned or any`
  line `class of those proceedings specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The proceedings referred to in sub-section (1) are the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings under Bengal Regulation 5, 1799 (to limit the Interference of the Zillah and City`
  line `Courts of Dewanny Adawlut in the Execution of Wills and Administration to the Estates of persons`
  line `dying intestate);`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) proceedings under the Indian Succession Act, 1865 (10 of 1865),^4`
  line `and the Probate and`
  line `Administration Act, 1881 (5 of 1881)4 which cannot be disposed of by District Delegates; and`
  line
  line `(e) references by Collectors under section 322C of the Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882)^5.`
  line
  line `(3) The District Judge may withdraw any such proceedings taken cognizance of by, or`
  line `transferred to, a Subordinate Judge or Munsif, and may either himself dispose of them or`
  line `transfer them to a Court under his administrative control competent to dispose of them.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 23.-- In sub-section (2) of section 23 of the said Act, --`
  line
  line `1) in clause (d) for the words and figures "the Indian Succession Act, 1865, and the`
  line `Probate and Administration Act, 1881", the words and figures "the Indian Succession`
  line `Act, 1925", shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(2) in clause (e), for the word and figures "section 322C", the words "paragraph 5 of`
  line `the Third Scheduled" shall be substituted and after the words "Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure" the figure "1908" shall be added.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 6 of 1935, s. 6]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 23 of Act XII of 1887.-- In sub-section (2) Section 23 of the said Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (d), for the words and figures "the Indian Succession Act, 1865, and the probate and`
  line `Administration Act, 1881". The words and figures "the Indian Succession Act, 1925" shall be substituted`
  line `; and`
  line
  line `(ii) clause (e) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 12 of 1960, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 23 does not apply to Honorary Munsifs and Benches in the U. P.: See the U.P. Honorary Munsifs Act, 1896 (U.P. 2 of`
  line `1896), s. 13.`
  line
  line `2. Clause (b) relating to proceedings under Act 40 of 1858 or Act 9 of 1861 rep. by Act 8 of 1890, s. 2 and Sch.`
  line
  line `3. Clause (c) relating to applications for certificates under Act 27 of 1860 was rep. by Act 7 of 1889.`
  line
  line `4. See now the Indian Succession Act, 1925 (39 of 1925). In Bengal and Assam, this cl. has been formally amended by Ben. Act`
  line `19 of 1935 and Assani Act 6 of 1935, respectively.`
  line
  line `5. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908), Sch. III. This cl. has been omitted in Bengal by Ben. Act 19 of`
  line `1935 and formally amended in Assam by Assam Act 6 of 1935.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (43043)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Disposal of proceedings referred to in last foregoing section.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43043&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1(1) Proceedings taken`
  line `cognizance of by, or transferred to, a Subordinate Judge or Munsif, as the case may be, under the last foregoing section shall be disposed of by him subject to the rules applicable to like`
  line `proceedings when disposed of by the District Judge:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal from an order of the Munsif in any such proceedings shall lie to the District`
  line Judge.
  line
  line `(2) An appeal from the order of the District Judge on the appeal from the order of a`
  line `munsif under this section shall lie to the High Court if a further appeal from the order of the`
  line `District Judge is allowed by the law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ss. 24 and 25 do not apply to Honorary Munsifs and Benches in the U.P.; see the U.P. Honorary Munsifs Act, 1896 (U.P. 2 of`
  line `1896), s. 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (43044)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to invest Subordinate Judges and Munsifs with Small Cause Court jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43044&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Power to invest Subordinate Judges and Munsifs with Small Cause Court`
  line `Jurisdiction.--The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, confer, within`
  line `such local limits as it thinks fit, upon any Subordinate Judge or Munsif the jurisdiction of a`
  line `Judge of a Court of Small Causes under the Provinicial Small Cause Courts Act, 1887`
  line `(9 of 1887) for the trial of suits, cognizable by such Courts, up to such value not exceeding five`
  line hundred^2
  line `rupees in the case of a Subordinate Judge or ^3[two hundred and fifty^4 rupees] in the case`
  line `of a Munsif as it thinks fit, and may withdraw any jurisdiction so conferred:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, delegate to the`
  line `High Court its powers under this section.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 25.-- In section 25 of the said Act, for the words "five hundred rupees", the`
  line `words dbqrsseven hundred and fifty rupees" and for the words "two hundred and fifty rupees", the words`
  line `"three hundred rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 6 of 1935, s. 7]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 25.--For section 25 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil Courts Act, 1887 the following section shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"25. The State Government may, by notification in the Gazette, confer within such local limits as`
  line `it thinks fit, upon any Civil Judge or Munsif the jurisdiction of a Judge of a Court of Small Causes`
  line `under the Provincial Small Causes Courts Act, 1887, for the trial of suits cognizable by such Coutts,`
  line `upto such value not exceeding one thousand rupees in the case of a Civil Judge or five hundred rupee`
  line `in the case of a Munsif as it thinks fit, and may withdraw any jurisdiction so conferred:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, by notification in the Gazette delegate to the High`
  line `Court its powers under the section."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 14 of 1970, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 25 of Act XII of 1887--Section 25 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil Courts`
  line `Act, 1887, as amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh shall be re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof,`
  line and--
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), as so re-numbered, for the existing proviso, the following proviso shall be`
  line `substituted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"Provided that in relation to suits of the nature referred to in the proviso to sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 15 of the said Act the references in this sub-section to one thousand rupees and five`
  line `hundred rupees shall be construed respectively as references to five thousand rupees and one`
  line `thousand rupees.";`
  line
  line `(ii) after sub-section (1) as so re-numbered, the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely :---`
  line
  line `"(2) The State Government may by notification in the official Gazette, confer upon any`
  line `District Judge or Additional District Judge he jurisdiction of a Judge of a Court of Small Causes`
  line `under the Provincial Small Cause Courts Act, 1887, for the trial of all suits (irrespective of their`
  line `value), by the lesser for the eviction of a lessee from a building after the determination of his`
  line `lease, or for the recovery from him of rent in respect of the period of occupation thereof during`
  line `the continuance of the lease or of compensation for the use and occupation thereof after such`
  line `determination of lease, and may withdraw any jurisdiction so conferred.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "building" has the same`
  line `meaning as in Article (4) in the Second Schedule to the said Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may by notification in the official Gazette delegate to the High`
  line `Court its powers under this section."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 37 of 1972, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 25 --In section 25 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1) as amended from time`
  line `to time in its application to Uttar Pradesh,-`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "one thousand rupees" and "five hundred rupees" the words "two thousand`
  line `rupees" and "one thousand rupees" shall respectively he substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the proviso, as substituted by the Uttar Pradesh Civil Laws Amendment Act, 1972, the`
  line `following proviso shall be substituted, namely :-`
  line
  line `"Provided that in relation to suits of the nature referred to in the proviso to sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 15 of the said Act the reference in this sub-section to two thousand rupees and one`
  line `thousand rupees shall be construed respectively as references to five thousand rupees and two`
  line `thousand rupees."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 57 of 1976, s. 28]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 25--.In section 25 of the principal Act,-`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-sections (1) the following sub-sections shall be substituted, namely`
  line `:---`
  line
  line `"(1) The High Court may by notification in the official Gazette, confer`
  line `within such local limits as it thinks fit, upon any Civil Judge or Munsif the`
  line `jurisdiction of a Judge of a Court of Small Causes under the Provincial Small`
  line `Cause Courts Act, 1887 for the trial of suits cognizable by such Courts. up to`
  line `such value not exceeding five thousand rupees as it thinks fit and may`
  line `withdraw any jurisdiction so conferred :"`
  line
  line `Provided that in relation to suits of the nature referred to in the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15 of the said Act, the reference in this sub-section to`
  line `five thousand rupees shall be construed as reference to twenty five thousand`
  line `rupees.;"`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2), for the words State Government the word High Court`
  line `shall be substituted ;`
  line
  line `(c) sub-section (3) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 17 of 1991, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Section 25 of the Bengal, Agra and Assam Civil Courts Act, 1887, as amended in its application to Uttar`
  line `Pradesh shall be re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof, and--`
  line
  line `"Provided that in relation to suits of the nature referred to in the proviso to sub-section (3) of section`
  line `15 of the said Act the references in this sub-section to one thousand rupees and five hundred rupees shall`
  line `be constructed respectively as references to five thousand rupees and one thousand rupees."`
  line
  line `(ii) after sub-section (1) as so re-numbered, the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"(2) The State Government may by notification in the official Gazette confer upon any District`
  line `Judge or Additional District Judge the jurisdiction of a Judge of a Court Act, 1887, for the trial of all`
  line `suits (irrespective of their value), by the lessor for the eviction of a lessee from a building after the`
  line `determination of his lease, or for the recovery from him of rent in respect of the period of occupation`
  line `thereof during the continuance of the lease or of compensation for the use and occupation thereof`
  line `after such determination of lease, and may withdraw any jurisdiction so conferred.`
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purpose of this sub-section, the expression building has the same`
  line `meaning as in Article (4) in the Second Schedule to the said Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may by notification in the official Gazette delegate to the High Court`
  line `its powers under this section."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 37 of 1972, s. 5]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 25 of Act XII of 1887. -- In Section 25 of the said Act, for the words "five`
  line `hundred rupees", the words "seven hundred and fifty rupees" and for the words "two hundred and fifty`
  line `rupees", the words "three hundred rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 12 of 1960, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908), Sch. III. This cl. has been omitted in Bengal by Ben. Act 19 of`
  line `1935 and formally amended in Assam by Assam Act 6 of 1935.`
  line
  line `2. In Bengal and Assam the limits are seven hundred and fifty and three hundred, respectively: see Ben. Act 19 of 1935 and`
  line `Assam Act 6 of 1935.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 1911, s. 4, for "one hundred rupees".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by 4 of 1914, s. 2 and Sch., Pt. I.`
