obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may`
  line `invest with the powers of any Civil Court under this Act, by name or in virtue of office,"`
  line
  line `(a) any officer in the Chutia Nagpur, ^1[Sambalpur], Jalpaiguri or Darjeeling District, or`
  line `in any part of the territories administered by the Chief Commissioner of Assam except the`
  line `district of Sylhet, or,`
  line
  line `(b) after consultation with the High Court, any officer serving in any other part of the territories`
  line `to which this Act extends and belonging to a class defined in this behalf by the State Government`
  line `^2*** .`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in ^3[sections 4, 5, 6, 8, 10 or 11] applies to any officer so invested, but all the`
  line `other provisions of this Act shall, so far as those provisions can be made applicable, apply to`
  line `him as if he were a Judge of the Court with the powers of which he is invested.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, in the territories mentioned in clause (a) of sub-section (1), the same local`
  line `jurisdiction is assigned to two or more officers invested with the powers of a Munsif, the officer`
  line `invested with the powers of a District Judge may, with the previous sanc tion of the State`
  line `Government, delegate his functions under sub-section (2) of section 13 to an officer invested`
  line `with the powers of a Subordinate Judge or to one of the officers invested with the powers of a`
  line Munsif.
  line
  line `(4) Where the place at which the Court of an officer invested with powers under`
  line `sub-section (1) is to be held has not been fixed under section 14, the Court may be held at any`
  line `place within the local limits of its jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 36.-- In section 36 of the principal Act, in clause (a) of sub-section (1),`
  line `for the words "territories administered by the Chief Commissioner of Assam except the district`
  line `of Sylhet" occurring between the words "the" and "or" the words "State of Assam" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 9 of 1965, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by 4 of 1906, s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. The words "with the previous sanction of the G. G. in C." rep. by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule,`
  line `Part I.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "sections 4 to 8 (both inclusive), or sections 10 to 12 (both inclusive), or sections 27 to 35 (both inclusive)".`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (43056)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Certain decisions to be according to Native law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43056&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1(1) Where in any suit or other`
  line `proceeding it is necessary for a Civil Court to decide any question regarding succession,`
  line `inheritance, marriage or caste, or any religious usage or institution, the Muhammadan law in`
  line `cases where the parties are Muhammadans, and the Hindu law in cases where the parties arc`
  line `Hindus, shall form the rule of decision except in so far as such law has, by legislative enactment,`
  line `been altered or abolished.`
  line
  line `(2) In cases not provided for sub-section (1) or by any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `the Court shall act according to justice, equity and good conscience.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The provisions of this section, in so far as they are inconsistent with- the provisions of the Muslim Personal Law (Shariat)`
  line `Application Act, 1937 (26 of 1937), rep. by s. 6 of that Act, but have been revived by s. 3 of Act 16 of 1943.`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (43057)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Judges not to try suits in which they are interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43057&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The presiding officer of a`
  line `Civil Court shall not try any spit or other proceeding to which he is a party or in which he is`
  line `personally interested.`
  line
  line `(2) The presiding officer of an appellate Civil Court under this Act shall not try an appeal against a`
  line `decree or order passed by himself in another capacity.`
  line
  line `(3) When any such suit, proceeding or appeal as is referred to in sub-section (1) or`
  line `subsection (2) comes before any such officer, the officer shall forthwith transmit the record of`
  line `the case to the Court to which he is immediately subordinate, with a report of the`
  line `circumstances attending the reference.`
  line
  line `(4) The superior Court shall thereupon dispose of the case under section 25 of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure (14 of 1882)^1.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the extraordinary original civil`
  line `jurisdiction of the High Court.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Amendment of section 38.-- In sub-section (4) of section 38 of the said Act, for the words and figures`
  line `"section 25 of the Code of Civil Procedure", the words and figures "section 24 of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 6 of 1935, s. 8]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 38 of Act XII of 1887. -- In sub-section (4) of Section 38 of the said Act, for the`
  line `words and figures "Section 25 of the Code of Civil Procedure", the words and figures "Section 24 of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[ Bihar Act 12 of 1960, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See now s. 24 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908). In Bengal and Assam, that reference has been formally`
  line `subs. by Ben. Act 19 of 1935 and Assam Act 6 of 1935 respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (43058)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Subordination of Courts to District Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43058&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the last foregoing`
  line `section the presiding officer of a Court subject to the administrative control of the District`
  line `Judge shall be deemed to be immediately subordinate to the Court of the District Judge, and,`
  line `for the purposes of the Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882), the Court of such an officer`
  line `shall be deemed to be of a grade inferior to that of the Court of the District Judge.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `In Section 39 of the Said Act, after the words "Code of Civil Procedure", the figures "1908" shall be`
  line inserted.
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 6 of 1935, s. 4]`
  line
  line Bihar
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 39 of Act XII of 1887. -- In Section 39 of the said Act, after the words "Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure", the figures "1908" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Bihar Act 12 of 1960, s. 8]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (43059)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Application of Act to State Courts of Small Causes .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065&sectionId=43059&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00027_188712_1523273842065
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) This section and sections 15,`
  line `32, 37, 38 and 39 apply to Courts of Small Causes constituted under the Provincial Small Cause`
  line `Courts Act, 1887 (9 of 1887).`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided by that Act, the other sections of this Act do not apply to those`
  line Courts.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
